put.summary:
Upsert an extended property to an existing sales order. This will update a sales order extended property if the
                same key exists and

parameters.description: The property value for the property that is to be created.

post.summary:
Submit Order to GCM Quote Order Service.


The enableBulkOrders flag in submitOrderModel will default to false if the

submitOrderModel is not passed in the body of the request.


This enableBulkOrders flag was designed to be used when a client needs to submit

several orders at the same time. When this flag is set to true, each fulfillment

unit ID will be updated with a new GUID.

By default this route calls GCMP CreateOrder action method, Set IsSubmitOrder Flag to true if GCMP SubmitOrder needs to be called for the online orders

200.description: Submits the order to GCM QuoteOrder Service and return the Processing results

put.summary:
Updates smart price for sales order.


The fully populated model must be passed or you will get a BadRequest

response. In other words, if a property from the model is missing in

your call to this endpoint, you will get a BadRequest response.


If your intention is to set a property in the model to null, just include that

property in your call and the value for that property will be set to null.

204.description: Successfully updated smart prices.

400.description: Returned when the model is not specified or missing one or more properties.

property in your call and the value for that property will be set to null.
